Summary:
During the test execution phase of the E-Commerce Application v1.0, all 5 test cases executed resulted in failures. The identified issues span across critical functionalities including user authentication, shopping cart operations, and checkout processes. Two critical-severity bugs were identified (BUG-02 and BUG-05) that require immediate remediation before proceeding to the next testing phase.

Key Findings:
- Authentication module has blocking issues preventing user login with valid credentials
- Shopping cart functionality is non-responsive to user interactions
- Pricing calculations fail to update in real-time
- Product display issues affecting user experience
- Discount/coupon application contains logic errors

Recommendations:
1. Prioritize resolution of critical-severity bugs (BUG-02, BUG-05)
2. Conduct code review for shopping cart module (BUG-01, BUG-03)
3. Verify image asset delivery mechanism (BUG-04)
4. Re-execute test suite after bug fixes
5. Implement automated regression testing for affected modules

